---
title: Mediterranean Grilling Cheese Bowls with Couscous, Carrots, and Harissa Crema
description: Cheese Louise! Will ya look at those sear marks! Thanks to its high melting point, the cheese in this recipe stays firm when you warm it in a pan while simultaneously developing a browned, slightly crisp exterior. In other words, pure dairy deliciousness. It would probably taste good with anything, although we think the spicy harissa carrots, Israeli couscous, and lemony arugula give it some stellar Mediterranean vibes.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mediterranean-grilling-cheese-bowls-548f4d1c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mediterranean-grilling-cheese-bowls-5af452e530006c41876951a2-f4f74bc4.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 890 kcal
  fat: 62 g
  saturated fat: 28 g
  carbohydrates: 45 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 800 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mediterranean-grilling-cheese-bowls-5af452e530006c41876951a2
course: main course
cuisine: Mediterranean
---

Wash and dry all produce. Peel @carrots{2%unit}. Using your #peeler{}, shave
carrots lengthwise into ribbons. Cut @grilling cheese{8%ounce} into 1-inch
cubes. Zest 1 tsp zest from @lemon{1%unit}, then cut into quarters. Melt
@butter{1%tablespoon} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add
@Israeli couscous{1/2%cup}, tossing to coat. Cook until toasted,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pour 2 cups water into #pot with couscous and bring to a boil, then lower heat
and reduce to a simmer. Cook until al dente, ~{7-8%minutes}, then drain and
transfer to a medium #bowl. Stir in juice from one lemon quarter and a drizzle
of @olive oil{}. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

While couscous cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #pan over medium-high
heat. Add carrots and half the @harissa powder{1%tablespoon}, tossing to coat.
Cook, tossing, until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in a squeeze of lemon. Season
with salt and pepper. Set aside off heat until couscous is done. After seasoning
couscous, toss carrots into couscous in bowl.

Place @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, juice from one lemon quarter, remaining
harissa, and @olive oil{2%tablespoon} in a medium #bowl. Season with salt and
pepper. Whisk to combine.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{3%tablespoon} in a large #pan over medium-high heat
(use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add cheese to pan and cook, turning
cubes until browned all over, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Add @arugula{2%ounce} to bowl with crema and toss to coat, then divide between
bowls for serving. Top with carrot and couscous mixture as well as cheese.
Garnish with lemon zest. Serve with any remaining lemon quarters on the side for
squeezing over.

> Cheese Louise! Will ya look at those sear marks! Thanks to its high melting
